00:00:00.120 --> 00:00:03.960
&gt;&gt; Hello everyone, my name is
Anne Savage and I work at the,

00:00:03.960 --> 00:00:07.480
in the Education Department
at the Library of Congress.

00:00:07.480 --> 00:00:13.560 position:69%
We are thrilled to welcome you to the second
annual Online Conference for Educators.

00:00:13.560 --> 00:00:17.500
Our session today, Library
of Congress 101 for Teachers

00:00:17.500 --> 00:00:20.730 position:72%
and now I would like to introduce our speaker.

00:00:20.730 --> 00:00:24.110 position:73%
Our speaker for this evening is Cheryl Lederle.

00:00:24.110 --> 00:00:28.660
She has worked as an Educational
Resources Specialist at the Library

00:00:28.660 --> 00:00:31.500
of Congress since December of 2003.

00:00:31.500 --> 00:00:35.290
In that role, she has advanced
the library's educational mission

00:00:35.290 --> 00:00:40.290 position:58%
by providing professional development
both in person and via webinar.

00:00:40.290 --> 00:00:45.260 position:61%
She's also played a significant role in
shaping the library's online repository

00:00:45.260 --> 00:00:51.670 position:56%
of classroom materials and resources
for teachers at loc.gov/teachers,

00:00:51.670 --> 00:00:56.320
and she continues to contribute to
the development of those materials.

00:00:56.320 --> 00:00:59.650 position:73%
Cheryl has 15 years experience teaching English

00:00:59.650 --> 00:01:04.120
at both the high school and
community college levels.

00:01:04.120 --> 00:01:05.670
Welcome, Cheryl.

00:01:05.670 --> 00:01:10.850 position:63%
&gt;&gt; Thanks Ann, and welcome to all of
you who I expect have taught a full day,

00:01:10.850 --> 00:01:16.800 position:61%
and I appreciate that you are
choosing to spend your evening with us.

00:01:16.800 --> 00:01:23.150 position:72%
I want to explore what the Library of Congress
has for teachers, looking particularly

00:01:23.150 --> 00:01:25.160 position:63%
at lesson plans and primary source sets,

00:01:25.160 --> 00:01:28.000
webinars and professional
development opportunities.

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:34.010 position:69%
And then I want to spend just a little bit
of time introducing you to what's behind all

00:01:34.010 --> 00:01:38.640 position:56%
of these teacher materials and we'll
explore very briefly ways to tap

00:01:38.640 --> 00:01:43.120
into those vast library collections
to find even more.

