00:06:18.720 --> 00:06:23.070
And we started developing those
when in conversation with teachers

00:06:23.070 --> 00:06:26.530 position:61%
about using the lesson plans that we've
been publishing for quite a number

00:06:26.530 --> 00:06:33.080 position:59%
of years we realized that teachers are
taking apart the lesson plans looking

00:06:33.080 --> 00:06:38.340
for primary sources of use
and then for teaching ideas

00:06:38.340 --> 00:06:41.280
and this sounded very familiar
from my days as a teacher.

00:06:41.280 --> 00:06:46.890 position:58%
I didn't teach somebody else's lesson
plan but I loved to mine their ideas.

00:06:46.890 --> 00:06:51.030 position:73%
And so we put the primary source sets together.

00:06:51.030 --> 00:06:57.120 position:75%
It's 18 primary sources on a particular theme or
topic and there are more than 30 of these now.

00:06:57.120 --> 00:07:04.350 position:75%
And then each one we wrap in a teacher's guide--
looks about like this, this is the top of it--

00:07:04.350 --> 00:07:09.030
with a brief historical background
about the theme or topic.

00:07:09.030 --> 00:07:15.480
And then in additional also
teaching ideas for it.

00:07:15.480 --> 00:07:22.660 position:59%
Each primary source set also links to
the teacher's guides an analysis tool.

00:07:22.660 --> 00:07:28.720 position:72%
And several of the presentations during the
online conference have made reference to this.

00:07:28.720 --> 00:07:37.150 position:66%
The analysis tool looks pretty simple
because the design of it is pretty simple.

00:07:37.150 --> 00:07:43.260
It is three columns-- observe,
reflect, and question.

00:07:43.260 --> 00:07:48.640
And then an invitation for
students to think about what they'd

00:07:48.640 --> 00:07:52.650 position:63%
like to investigate to learn more about.

00:07:52.650 --> 00:07:59.930 position:75%
The process itself is way less simple and that's
reflected in the upper right corner of this,

00:07:59.930 --> 00:08:04.260
the circular arrow that says
observe, reflect, and question.

00:08:04.260 --> 00:08:09.940 position:59%
And we recognize that it is not at all
a linear process but flat paper sort

00:08:09.940 --> 00:08:12.510 position:63%
of limits our ability to represent that.

00:08:12.510 --> 00:08:14.930
So we've done what we can.

00:08:14.930 --> 00:08:19.580
You'll notice if you look,
that it's available by,

00:08:19.580 --> 00:08:22.860 position:72%
